shall
come
upon
us,
and
if
it
shall
be
what
it
gives
signs
of
being,
it
is
high
time
to
be
careful
for
ourselves,
or
we
may
prove
to
be
the
basest
and
worst
of
men
in
the
sight
of
heaven
and
earth,
in
the
sight
of
friends
and
enemies.”
When
the
soldiers
heard
this
they
wondered
what
it
could
be,
and
told
him
to
speak.
So
he
began
again:
“You
remember
at
Cerastis
there
were
some
native
