they
had;
and
I
think
some
of
you
went
to
the
nearest
one,
and
bought
things
and
came
back.
Captain
Clearetos
learnt
this,
and
heard
it
was
a
small
place,
and
unguarded
because
they
thought
themselves
friends.
So
he
marched
up
there
at
night,
to
sack
the
place,
without
saying
a
word
to
any
