6.1
After
this,
while
the
delay
lasted,
they
lived
partly
from
the
market
and
partly
by
making
raids
on
Paphlagonia.
The
Paphlagonians,
too,
were
quite
clever
at
kidnapping
stragglers,
and
they
tried
to
damage
those
who
were
camped
far
out;
in
consequence,
both
sides
were
bitterly
hostile.
At
last
Corylas,
who
then
was
the
ruler
of
Paphlagonia,
sent
