what
they
call
the
Harvest
Song.
The
method
of
dancing
is,
that
one
lays
down
his
arms,
and
sows,
and
drives
the
plow,
turning
again
and
again
as
in
fear.
A
raider
approaches;
the
other
looks
out,
and
picks
up
